# Gamentic - publish the GAME CODE only. Everything design/process/secret stays local.

# --- secrets & environment ---
.env
**/.env
*.key
*.pem

# --- agentic / process / research / session markers (kept private) ---
.research/
.agents/
.codex/
.claude/
session
sessiontts
sessionfrontend
imagesession
sessionimage
session2
expert

# local screen recordings (never repo material)
Screencast*.mp4

# --- all documentation, specs, contracts, plans (kept private) ---
# NOTE: orchestrator/prompts/*.md are runtime game code, NOT docs - they stay tracked.
# The root README.md IS public (the project's face); every other README/doc stays private.
# EXCEPTION: the public docs site (GitHub Pages) - the interactive atlases, the hub, and
# the agent-ready guide. Everything else under docs/ (HANDOFF, shared, lane folders,
# feedback) stays private. Ignore docs/ contents, then re-include only the site.
docs/*
!docs/.nojekyll
!docs/index.html
!docs/guide/
# build scratch for the docs site (template + generators), never published
.docbuild/
**/README.md
!/README.md
**/ARCHITECTURE.md
**/PLAN.md
**/REDESIGN.md
**/CHANGELOG.md
!/CHANGELOG.md
**/SPECS.md

# --- runtime data, generated media, databases ---
**/data/
voice-api/samples/
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# --- python ---
**/.venv/
**/.venv-test/
**/__pycache__/
**/.pytest_cache/
*.pyc

# --- node / frontend build ---
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/

# --- frontend design mockups / screenshots (private) ---
frontend/examples/

# --- os cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
